#Antidote: against poisons
Activated charcoal: small pores increase surface, adsorbs ingested poisons
Antivenom: made by injecting toxin into animal and extracting antibodies from blood

#Bacteria
Clostridium botulinum: botox (neurotoxin)

#Plants
Toxalbumin: cytotoxic protein, disables ribosomes
- Ricinus communis: ricin
- Abrus precatorius: abrin
Nerium oleander

#Fungi
Amatoxin: disables RNA polymerase
- Amanita, Galerina, Lepiota
Rubroboletus satanas: bloody diarrhea

#Animals
Tetrodotoxin: neurotoxin, blocks sodium channel
Conidae (cone snails): neurotoxins
Hapalochlaena (blue ringed octopus): tetrodotoxin
Cubozoa (box jellyfish): cytotoxic, neurotoxic
Pterois (lionfish)
Synanceia (stonefish): verrucotoxin (affects calcium and potassium channels), stonustoxin
Tetraodontidae (pufferfish): tetrodotoxin (neurotoxin)

#Scorpiones
neurotoxins, affect membrane channels

#Spiders
Atrax (funnel web)
- delta atracotoxin: neurotoxic, affects sodium channels
Hadronyche (funnel web): similar to Atrax
Latrodectus (widow): neurotoxic
Phoneutria (banana):
Loxosceles (recluse):

#Snakes
Three-finger toxins: neurotoxins
Elapidae: mainly neurotoxic, also cardiotoxic and cytotoxic
- Bungarus (krait)
- Oxyuranus (taipan): taipoxin
- Dendroaspis (mamba): dendrotoxin, affects potassium channels
- Naja (cobra): spit in eye, cytotoxic
- Ophiophagus (king cobra)
Viperidae: mainly hemotoxic, also neurotoxic
- Crotalus (rattlesnake): crotoxin, crotamine
- Daboia
- Echis
